        "Source": "ANSA"
      }
    ],
    "Description": "Package updates are available for Anolis 8 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\n\nCVE-2022-29824:\nIn libxml2 before 2.9.14, several buffer handling functions in buf.c (xmlBuf*) and tree.c (xmlBuffer*) don't check for integer overflows. This can result in out-of-bounds memory writes. Exploitation requires a victim to open a crafted, multi-gigabyte XML file. Other software using libxml2's buffer functions, for example libxslt through 1.1.35, is affected as well.",
    "Advisory": {
      "Severity": "Moderate",
      "Issued": {
        "Date": "2022-07-08"
      },
      "Updated": {
        "Date": "2022-07-09"
      },
      "Cves": [
